### Payment Gateway Webhook — ACCT-04
### Tests the inbound async notification endpoint for payment gateways.
### HMAC signatures below are for local dev only (secret = "test-secret").
### Usage: VS Code REST Client extension.

@host = http://localhost:8080
@tenant_id = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
@provider = STRIPE

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Stripe payment.captured event (no HMAC — dev mode only)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/v1/billing/webhooks/payment-gateway?tenant_id={{tenant_id}}&provider={{provider}}
Content-Type: application/json
Stripe-Signature: t=1700000000,v1=abc123

{
  "id": "evt_test_capture_001",
  "type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "id": "pi_test_001",
      "amount": 15000,
      "currency": "usd",
      "status": "succeeded"
    }
  }
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 2. Stripe payment.failed event
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/v1/billing/webhooks/payment-gateway?tenant_id={{tenant_id}}&provider={{provider}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "evt_test_fail_001",
  "type": "payment_intent.payment_failed",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "id": "pi_test_002",
      "amount": 5000,
      "currency": "usd",
      "status": "requires_payment_method"
    }
  }
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 3. Stripe refund.completed event
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/v1/billing/webhooks/payment-gateway?tenant_id={{tenant_id}}&provider={{provider}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "evt_test_refund_001",
  "type": "charge.refunded",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "id": "ch_test_001",
      "amount": 15000,
      "refunded": true
    }
  }
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 4. Stripe chargeback/dispute event
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/v1/billing/webhooks/payment-gateway?tenant_id={{tenant_id}}&provider={{provider}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "evt_test_dispute_001",
  "type": "charge.dispute.created",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "id": "dp_test_001",
      "charge": "ch_test_001",
      "amount": 15000,
      "currency": "usd",
      "reason": "fraudulent"
    }
  }
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 5. Stripe authorization.expired event
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/v1/billing/webhooks/payment-gateway?tenant_id={{tenant_id}}&provider={{provider}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "evt_test_auth_exp_001",
  "type": "payment_intent.canceled",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "id": "pi_test_auth_001",
      "status": "canceled",
      "cancellation_reason": "expired"
    }
  }
}

###

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 6. Duplicate event (idempotency check — should return 200 with received:true but SKIPPED)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POST {{host}}/v1/billing/webhooks/payment-gateway?tenant_id={{tenant_id}}&provider={{provider}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": "evt_test_capture_001",
  "type": "payment_intent.succeeded",
  "data": {
    "object": {
      "id": "pi_test_001",
      "amount": 15000,
      "currency": "usd",
      "status": "succeeded"
    }
  }
}
